<recipe>
<title>
Bacon Artichoke Baked Dip
</title>
<details>

</details>
<ingredients>
1 (8-ounce) package 1/3-less-fat cream cheese, softened
1/2 c . plain , non-fat Greek yogurt
3 garlic cloves , minced
1 tsp . Italian seasoning , divided
1/4 tsp . crushed red pepper
1/4 tsp . smoked paprika
3/4 c . grated Parmesan cheese , divided
4 bacon slices , cooked and crumbled, divided
1 c . marinated quartered artichoke hearts , drained, squeezed, and chopped
</ingredients>
<instructions>
Preheat oven to 350 F. Lightly grease a small baking dish.
In a medium bowl, stir together cream cheese and Greek yogurt until well-combined.
Stir in garlic, 3/4 tsp. Italian seasoning, red pepper, and paprika.
Stir in 1/2 cup Parmesan cheese, 3 slices crumbled bacon, artichoke hearts.
Spread into prepared baking dish.
Sprinkle with remaining Parmesan cheese and crumbled bacon.
Bake for 15-25 minutes, or until hot.
Sprinkle with remaining 1/4 tsp. Italian seasoning.
</instructions>
</recipe>
